
[1]forbearance

   FORBEARANCE, n.

   1. The act of avoiding, shunning or omitting; either the cessation or
   intermission of an act commenced, or a withholding from beginning an
   act. Liberty is the power of doing or forbearing an action, according
   as the doing or forbearance has a preference in the mind. The
   forbearance of sin is followed with satisfaction of mind.

   2. Command of temper; restraint of passions.

   3. The exercise of patience; long suffering; indulgence towards those
   who injure us; lenity; delay of resentment or punishment.

   Or despisest thou the riches of his goodness, and forbearance, and long
   suffering? Rom. 2.
